HEADWORD: Almond furnace
<hw>Al"mond fur`nace</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[Prob. a corruption of
<ets>Almain furnace</ets>, <it>i. e.</it>, German furnace. See
<er>Almain</er>.]</ety> <def>A kind of furnace used in refining, to
separate the metal from cinders and other foreign matter.</def>
<rj><au>Chambers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

